					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10361007#post-4159862</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10361007/scp-3659#post-4159862</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 21 Feb 2019 00:32:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Weryllium</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2727655</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>OK so here's the thing. The glove itself is essentially Safe, and can be put in a Safe locker. But it's a package deal with the already existing and contained dinosaurs, which are living and thus cannot be Safe.</p> <p>Because I don't really know of a singular consensus on cases like this, I decided to err on the higher class and label the whole mess Euclid.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
